    A manager for controlling the loading and usage of any plugins being used. Each instance of Pathfinder has one of these, and it allows the user to load PathfinderPlugins, which are designed to allow developers to extend the normal limits of Pathfinder's customization. This is intended to be an internal class, so I'm not sure why you'd need to have access to this, but oh well.
